    <bioghist id="aspace_92ad15702daaf021a0af3ae8484f9769">
      <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
      <p>Dr. Messiah K. King and his wife Bertha King were members of the Metropolitan Baptist Church in Washington, D.C.. The Metropolitan Baptist Church was founded in Washington, D.C. in 1864 in a Quaker Civil War barracks.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <custodhist id="aspace_5b71f15a194e36a8aea9ac713c7a37f2">
      <head>Custodial History</head>
      <p>The collection was originally a part of the Library Washington Vertical File Collection. The materials were removed due to their unique nature among the "Church Series" of the Vertical File Collection. It is not known as to how the Library  acquired the materials.</p>
    </custodhist>
    <processinfo id="aspace_c739c459f404373834138a7fed3c007d">
      <head>Processing Information</head>
      <p>Basic archival processing procedures were applied to the collection when it was processed.</p>
    </processinfo>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_57e7cfca5f5d472583961c705f65cabe">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The items in this collection consist of correspondence, church bulletins and programs, a prayer book, and various early twentieth century ephemera.</p>
    </scopecontent>
